          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I check my <%=data.scheme_name%> status?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                You can check your <%=data.scheme_name%> application status by visiting the official website <%=data.resources.official_links.main_website%> and clicking on "Beneficiary Status." Enter your Aadhaar number or  registration number to view your status.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">Why Women?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                Women welfare schemes are designed to address issues faced by women, such as economic, social, political, and health disparities. These schemes recognize that women may have different needs and require targeted assistance to achieve equal access to resources and opportunities.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">I haven't received benefits of scheme. What should I do?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                Check your application status by visiting the local authorities or online sites if applied online. You can also contact your local municipal office or call the <%= data.scheme_name %> helpline at <%= data.contact_information.ministry_contact%>.
              </p>
            </div>
